REPROCESSED IN SXS 1.16 (2018-02-22 KE) Significant beaverdam activity. Unable to wade due to depth. Conventional measurement would have great difficulty due to slow velocities. Measurement conducted off of bridge using clothesline (no loop). Tether attached to boat in two locations (at carabiner/clothesline and transducer cup at front of boat) so as to enable proper alignment of ADCP in very low flow conditions (see photos). Allowed for no angles during section by section measurement. Second CC passed. Typical Heading Error: < 0.514°. Vector Addition Of Single And Double Cycle Errors: 0.578°. MBT as a loop would be virtually impossible. Three stationary tests were performed. Two of the tests indicated the error ‘Difference Upstream is negative’ likely due to such low velocities (0.034m/s average). Stabilization of boat with second line worked very well. 22 panels measured. Two exceed 10% (11 & 12%). Sources:Manual ==Mean gage height correction: Observed value=1.802 Correction=-0.004 ==

Flow observed on top of rotting ice in gauge pool. Could not wade across. Central portion of beaver-dam was known to be removed prior to last visit and therefore total flow (including any UIF) could be measured at this exact location. 10m clothesline set-up directly above beaver-dam.  Measurement file incorrectly named ‘07GE002_20160406’. Some ambiguity velocities occur (mostly at edges). Thought to be due to very low velocities and subsequent difficulty keeping boat tracking smoothly. Measured Q was less than 50% (33.14%). StreamPro should be used for these smaller cross-section measurements. Two transects exceed 10% missing data (004; 11% & 008; 22%). Missing data occurs mostly at edges. Standard deviation/mean exceeds 5% (9.7%). Compass Calibration passed (Vector Addition Of Single And Double Cycle Errors: 0.223°).  Moving Bed Test (loop) failed (FAIL: Moving Bed Vel. (MBV) < Minimum MBV Criteria; No Correction Recommended). However the water velocity is less than 0.24 m/s and could cause the loop method to be inaccurate. Due to the nature of this creek it is highly unlikely any moving bed would be present. Change due to suggested Extrap automatic fit is >1% (0.22% with Power/Power 0.1344) and therefore not applied.
